      },
      "date": "2012-07-24 14:54:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\nPatch looks fine. One question is how long ago was linux/version.h in use?  Maybe this could be removed if it is no longer needed for current kernels?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0d10ac826550843d94eba84f62a34435b361ecba",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 242,
        "name": "Liu Xuezhao",
        "email": "xuezhao.liu@emc.com",
        "username": "XuezhaoLiu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-07-24 17:19:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nthe inux/version.h exist till now. The \"UTS_RELEASE\" moved from inux/version.h to linux/utsrelease.h or generated/utsrelease.h since kernel 2.6.18 (kernel commit 63104eec234bdecb55fd9c15467ae00d0a3f42ac). \n\nSeems the last case \"else LINUXRELEASEHEADER=%kobjdir/in\nclude/linux/version.h\" can be removed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
